      "answer": "The study of the immediate causes of behavior based on physiology"
    },
    {
      "question": "Which part of the brain is primarily responsible for decision-making and impulse control?",
      "options": [
        "Occipital lobe",
        "Parietal lobe",
        "Frontal lobe",
        "Temporal lobe"
      ],
      "answer": "Frontal lobe"
    },
    {
      "question": "Why is it important for psychologists to understand the relationship between brain structures and behavior?",
      "options": [
        "To diagnose and treat disorders effectively",
        "To create more engaging video games",
        "To increase their social media following",
        "To design better office spaces"
      ],
      "answer": "To diagnose and treat disorders effectively"
    }
  ]
}
```

Take your time to think about each question, and let me know your answers when you're ready!
